Female. Small to medium (3.3–9.5mm) size spiders. Somatic morphology as in male, colouration somewhat darker and more contrasted than in males. LEGS : As in males, sometimes with pattern of yellow-orange to dark brown or blackish bands; with less leg spines; legs shorter than males compared to body length. Tarsal claw unipectinate, with 4 teeth and dense claw tufts. Pedipalp claw unipectinate with 4 short teeth. GENITALIA: Epigynum with strongly sclerotized median sector, either pentagonal (
